    <h1>How TruthStamp works.</h1>
    <p class="how-lead">
      In simple terms: you give us something to seal — a draft, a prediction, a contract, an idea — and we generate a permanent, verifiable receipt that proves exactly when it existed and that it hasn't been tampered with since. Here's the whole flow.
    </p>

    <!-- Step 1 -->
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Sign up — no wallet, no card needed</h3>
        <p>Create an account in 30 seconds with email or Google. The free tier lets you create up to 30 text receipts every month — no payment required, no credit card collected.</p>
        <p>Power users can optionally connect a Web3 wallet for advanced features, but it's never required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2 -->
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Drop your content into the composer</h3>
        <p>Type or paste the text you want to seal. Up to 500 characters per text receipt on the free tier; up to 5,000 on Pro. Add tags if you want to organize your receipts.</p>
        <p>On paid plans, you can also stamp files (PDFs, images, audio, video) and entire web pages.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3 -->
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Choose how visible the content is</h3>
        <p>You decide who can see your content. There are three options:</p>

        <div class="visibility-block">
          <p><strong>🌐 Public</strong> — Best for receipts you want to share. Your content is stored on a decentralized public storage layer; anyone with the link can view and verify it.</p>
          <p><strong>🔒 Sealed</strong> — Best for predictions. Your content is encrypted and hidden until a date you choose. On that date, it auto-reveals to the world — with mathematical proof you wrote it before any of it happened.</p>
          <p><strong>🔐 Hash-only</strong> — Best for confidential drafts and trade secrets. Only the cryptographic fingerprint is recorded; the actual content never leaves your device.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4 -->
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>We generate your receipt — in about 1 second</h3>
        <p>Behind the scenes: your content is hashed locally in your browser (creating a unique fingerprint), and that fingerprint is permanently sealed in our verification layer with the exact timestamp.</p>
        <p>The cryptographic proof is independent of TruthStamp's servers — anyone can verify it directly using public tools, even decades from now.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 5 -->
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Share your proof URL anywhere</h3>
        <p>You get a beautiful, permanent URL like <code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); background: var(--color-surface-alt); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">truthstamp.io/v/your-receipt-id</code> that displays your content alongside the verifiable timestamp and cryptographic proof.</p>
        <p>Share it on social media, embed it in an article, send it to a journalist, attach it to a contract — wherever you need to prove what you wrote and when.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why it works -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">Why this is different from a screenshot</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      Screenshots can be edited. Cloud notes can be backdated. Email timestamps can be spoofed. TruthStamp generates evidence that holds up because it's mathematically impossible to fake.
    </p>

    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-card">
        <h3>🔐 Cryptographically signed</h3>
        <p>Every receipt includes a cryptographic hash that mathematically proves the content hasn't been altered since stamping.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <h3>⏰ Timestamp from a third party</h3>
        <p>The timestamp comes from a public, decentralized verification layer — not from TruthStamp's servers, so it can't be manipulated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <h3>🌐 Independently verifiable</h3>
        <p>Anyone can verify your receipt using public tools — they don't have to trust TruthStamp's word for it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <h3>♾️ Survives our shutdown</h3>
        <p>The verification layer works without us. Even if TruthStamp closes tomorrow, your receipts remain provable forever.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Verification process -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">How verification works</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      When someone wants to verify your receipt, here's exactly what happens.
    </p>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>They open your proof URL</h3>
        <p>The page shows your content, the exact timestamp, and the cryptographic fingerprint that ties them together.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>They click "Verify independently"</h3>
        <p>Our verifier tool re-hashes the displayed content in their browser and compares it against the cryptographic record. If they match, the receipt is valid.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>They can also verify outside our website</h3>
        <p>Advanced users can verify the cryptographic record directly using public tools. We've open-sourced our verifier so anyone can run it locally — no trust in TruthStamp required. <a href="trust.html" style="color: var(--brand-primary); text-decoration: underline;">Learn more about our permanence promise →</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
